  "description": "The draw pile is the face-down stack from which [players](../../../terms/player.md) take new cards during setup or play in a [card game](../_index.md). After the [deck](./deck.md) is [shuffled](./shuffle.md) and [hands](./hand.md) are dealt, the remaining cards typically form the draw pile — a reservoir of hidden information that feeds new cards into the game.",
